definition: to support/to sustain/to erect/to raise/branch/division/to draw money/classifier for rods such as pens and guns, for army divisions and for songs or compositions
to support/to prop up/to push or move with a pole/to maintain/to open or unfurl/to fill to bursting point/brace/stay/support

sentences.english: Place the support frame at the bottom of the oil storage tank.
sentences.chinese: 放置支撑架于储油槽底下。

sentences.english: Clear the mist, water, fog set, supporting frames.
sentences.chinese: 排雾管，水箱，集雾器，支撑架等。

sentences.english: The bartender grins with his chin stuck out above the top of the white neck brace and asks, "Is this a test?"
sentences.chinese: 男招待戴着颈部支撑架咧嘴笑着问，“这是个测试？”

sentences.english: Remove the steering knuckle from the strut.
sentences.chinese: 拆去连接支撑架到球销的固定夹。

sentences.english: The inner mold support of a knee pipe is composed of the semi-circular arc-shaped support frames and a bivariate arc pad mold.
sentences.chinese: 弯管内模支撑由半圆弧形支撑架与双变弧垫模组成。

sentences.english: In these one can see the hanging knees made out of bloodwood.
sentences.chinese: 在这些人们可以看到支撑架是红木制作。

sentences.english: Particularly suitable for erection of scaffolding and heavy support frame surfaces.
sentences.chinese: 特别适合于搭设曲面脚手架和重载支撑架。

sentences.english: Chipped off coating on holder of umbrella.
sentences.chinese: 伞的支撑架覆盖层的缺口。

sentences.english: How would the support beams even reach to the bottom of the Pacific ocean?
sentences.chinese: 怎么把支撑架放进太平洋底？
